# Portfolio delivery assets (WebP / JPEG / compressed MP4) are small enough to
# ship through regular git — Git LFS is no longer used for them.
#
# Large PNG masters stay local and out of git (see
# bill/assets/portfolio/.gitignore). The generated .webp/.jpg/.mp4 files are the
# only media the site actually serves.
#
# NOTE: PNG masters and the two demo .mp4s were previously committed via LFS.
# Removing these rules does not retroactively un-LFS those existing blobs; the
# user can do that later with a non-destructive `git rm --cached` + re-add if
# desired. New commits of these file types use regular git.
